Package: GCalignR
Title: Simple Peak Alignment for Gas-Chromatography Data
Version: 0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(person("Martin", "Stoffel", email = "martin.adam.stoffel@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
             person("Meinolf", "Ottensmann", email = "meinolf.ottensmann@web.de", role = c("aut")))
Description: Aligns chromatography peaks with a three step algorithm: (1) Linear
    transformation of retention times to maximise shared peaks between samples
    (2) Align peaks within a certain error-interval (3) Merges rows that show
    complementary peak patterns and similar retention time means.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.2.3)
Imports: stringr,
        readr,
        magrittr,
        ggplot2,
        RColorBrewer,
        reshape2,
        pracma
License: GPL (>= 2)
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
Suggests: knitr,
          rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
